reviews.reviewbody:
I didn't want this one to end. Sequels generally are an embarrassment to the original works, but _Twenty Years After_ would work as well even if there had been no _Three Musketeers_. It stands on it's own. The story lines don't rehash _The Three Musketeers_. It has it's own pace & rhythm. The 4 definitely have matured & each has grown in his own way. I like this one better than the original.

The readers range from good to excellent. 

All in all, good stuff.
